### {231}{}{What can a saddened old man do in a cemetery? Obviously, I've come to remember the old days. Here is my son's grave. The inscription on the cross is almost erased, but I still have the sense not to forget his name and the location of the grave.}
{231}{}{一个悲伤的老人在墓地里能做什么？很明显，我开始怀念过去的日子了。这是我儿子的坟墓。十字架上的铭文几乎被抹去了，但我仍然有一种感觉，不要忘记他的名字和坟墓的位置。 -- What can a saddened old man do in a cemetery? Obviously, I've come to remember the old days. Here is my son's grave. The inscription on the cross is almost erased, but I still have the sense not to forget his name and the location of the grave.}
### {232}{}{Tell me how he died.}
